This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of convolutional networks also suggests that it could be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the adaptation of image classification networks, which could potentially place it under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as semantic segmentation, which could place it under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
